Token.Abstract: \@safecategory defines the implementation of a safe category named \a CATEGORY on \a CLASS. A safe category will only add methods to \a CLASS if a method by the same name does not already exist (\e not including superclasses). If \c DEBUG is defined and \c NDEBUG is not defined, any method conflicts will abort the application at startup; otherwise, any method conflicts are simply logged, and no overwriting occurs.
